6:
I'm begging you! Let me train under
you as your pupil!
10:
Well, this came out of nowhere. I
was wondering what you wanted to
talk about.
14:
I don't see why you would need
training. You're hardly required on
the battlefield...
17:
I get that, but I just want to be able
to protect myself if need be.
19:
Remember that weirdo mage? Who
knows when stuff like that's gonna
happen next.
22:
Fair point... Plus, I don't think it's
wrong of you to want to become
stronger.
26:
Right? I don't need to be a star
fighter or anything. I just want to get
good enough to buy everyone else
time.
28:
If I don't shape up, I'm gonna be
dragging Mili down forever!
33:
Keep in mind that my current body
is also not suited for combat. I'm not
sure how much I can teach you...
35:
However, if that does not bother you,
I will do my best as your mentor.
43:
We'll start by assessing your current
skills. If you can manage to land a
hit on me, you pass.
47:
Come on, there's no way I'm losing
to a fwuffy widdle bunny like you.
49:
I might not look it, but I work out, you
know?
54:
Then this little test will prove no
trouble for you. Now, begin!
60:
Are you kidding me?! I can't hit you
at all!
64:
What happened to that bravado
from before? We're just getting
started.
69:
Dammit! I'm gonna get you, even if it
takes me all day!
74:
Argh! No matter what I try, I keep
missing!
77:
From your movements and stamina,
I can see that you have, in fact,
honed your body. If that was all it
took, you'd hit me with ease.
79:
However, your attacks are far too
obvious. You're practically telling me
how and when you're going to
attack me.
89:
I'll just have to play my trump card!
Shamak!
98:
So that's what happens when that
spell fails, huh? Bit risky for a trump
card, don't you think?
103:
Let's end today's lesson here. As for
our future training...
105:
We'll need to teach you how to hide
your intentions from your opponent.
110:
Got it... So if I can manage to hit you,
we'll move onto the next stage, right?
114:
Right. However... You might learn
faster if you got some actual
combat experience.
118: In that case, I know just the place.
125:
Whoa! So there's even a world
covered in a huge forest...
128:
Unlike the Kaleidoscope, there are
no trapdoors or surprises here.
131:
Not to mention, it's great for
gathering ingredients for dinner!
146: Whoa! The heck is that thing?!
151:
Don't worry. Shroombo's a friend of
ours.
155:
Seriously? You sure he's not gonna
blind us with a green mist attack or
something?
158: No way. Go on, get a little closer.
172:
I can't tell if you're greeting me back
or threatening me...
176:
And that's exactly the sort of
attitude you need when
approaching the unknown. Better to
be cautious than careless.
181:
That being said, this is Shroombo
we're talking about. You'll be fine.
See? He wants to shake your hand.
191:
Not sure what you just said, but...
Like this?
195:
Whoa, that sent a shiver up my
spine...
200:
Reminds you of that monster in the
Kaleidoscope, doesn't it?
207:
(If this is all it takes to have me
shaking in my boots, I'm gonna be
useless to the others...)
221:
All right, now I'm ready for action! No
room for self doubt here!
223:
Alk, Light, you better not go easy on
me today! I'll take whatever you can
throw at me.
228:
Oh? Someone's motivated. Maybe
we should take him to the most
dangerous area next.
232:
Well, all right. But no complaining
once we're there.
238:
You got it! I'll show you both that I'm
no crybaby!
